# 1. PROJECT IDENTITY

## Project Name

LCAA

Legal Case & AI Assistant

---

## Vision

LCAA is designed to become a complete digital legal operating system.

The system is not merely a Progressive Web App (PWA).

The final goal is creating a professional legal platform capable of managing legal cases, documents, evidence, timelines, legal knowledge, AI assistance, and organizational workflows.

---

## Mission

Create a secure, intelligent, offline-capable legal environment for managing legal cases from the first document until the final judgment.

Every document must remain searchable.

Every action must remain documented.

Every decision must remain traceable.

Every change must remain version controlled.

---

# 2. CORE PRINCIPLES

The project follows these permanent principles.

## Principle 1

Documentation before coding.

No major feature shall be implemented before being documented.

---

## Principle 2

Architecture before implementation.

Every module must have a documented architecture.

---

## Principle 3

Security first.

User data is always more important than features.

---

## Principle 4

Offline first.

The system must continue working without Internet whenever possible.

---

## Principle 5

Single source of truth.

MASTER.md is the constitutional document of the project.

All other documents derive from MASTER.md.

---

## Principle 6

No undocumented changes.

Every architectural decision must be documented.

---

## Principle 7

Every version is reproducible.

Any released version should be rebuildable from Git.

