# AI ARCHITECTURE

Artificial Intelligence is one of the fundamental pillars of LCAA.

AI is designed to assist legal professionals, not replace them.

Every AI-generated output is considered a recommendation unless verified by the user.

The user always remains the final decision-maker.

---

## AI CORE OBJECTIVES

The AI Engine shall be capable of:

• Reading legal documents

• Understanding document relationships

• Summarizing documents

• Extracting important legal facts

• Building legal timelines

• Identifying contradictions

• Detecting missing evidence

• Assisting legal writing

• Producing structured reports

• Answering legal questions based on project data

